Function:
 	This standalone job is used to "de-link" load module or program object
        to NCALs.

Syntax:
        SUBMIT DELINK

Usage:
  	This job ran program binder (ex. linkage editor) to get a load module
        or program object map, then generate a sequence of program binder
        control statements using DFSORT to extract each control section to the
        separate member ("de-link).
        Specify data set names and member name on the lines 3-5 of the job.

        Please note: JCL features available since z/OS 2.1 is used.

        This job is an example how to do some meaningful things using standard
        tools only, without writing a program or even script.
